# Lab Title
Real-Time System Analysis

## Lab Overview
This lab explores the steps to gathering information about the dynamic aspects of processes, services and network connections

## Objectives

- Understand the the information that the dynamic process cmdlets provide
- Identify the  core cmdlets and syntax that are used by IT professionals
- Learn how these cmdlets are can impact the overall security of an organization

## Key Concepts

| Get-Process | Shows the processes currently running on a Windows system, such as Chrome, notepad, explorer |
| Get-Service | Shows  the services installed on a Windows system and their current status, such as Windows Update, Print Spooler, DHCP Client |
| Get-NetTCPConnection | Show current TCP network connections |
| Get-FileHash | Calculates the cryptographic hash of a file. By default, Powershell uses SHA256 |
| ADS(Alternate Data Streams) | Hidden secondary stream  of data that stores metadata, hidden scripts/payloads and downloaded files |
| PsPath | Property of Powershell. Shows the item's full location in Powershell provider format. Shows whether the provider is FileSystem, Registry, Certificate store, Environment variables, Alias or Function |
| PsParentPath | Shows the 'parent container' of an item in Powershell provider format. Does not show item |
| PSChildName | Shows the name of an item, without the full parent path |
| PSDrive | Which Powershell drive an item belongs to. Whether C, HKLM, HKCU, Env or Cert |
| PSProvider | Property that details which Powershell provider manages an item |
| PSIsContainer | property that states whether an item is a 'container'(file or folder). Returns either True or False |
| Stream | A piece of data attached to a file. Whether Success output, Error, Warning, Verbose, Debug or Information |
| $DATA | Default content stream of a file. Normal visible content |


