### Syntax: Get-Process

PS C:\Users\captain> Get-Process

Handles  NPM(K)    PM(K)      WS(K)     CPU(s)     Id  SI ProcessName 
-------  ------    -----      -----     ------     --  -- -----------
     67       5      872        500       0.06   2340   0 AggregatorHost
     55       5      712       2672       0.02   3024   0 AM_Delta_Patch_1.417.483.0
    309      13    18312       1256       0.52   1524   0 amazon-ssm-agent
     78       6     4440        944       0.02    516   0 cmd
     94       7     1224       1744       0.31    568   0 conhost
[...]

- details the processes running on the system at the moment
- Handles(number of OS-managed objects'the process is using)
- NPM(K)(Non-Paged Memory in KB, memory that stays in physical RAM)
- PM(K)(Paged Memory in KB, meory that can be 'paged out)
- WS(K)(Working Set in KB, physical RAM currently used)
- CPU(s)(total processor time the process has used since it started)
- ID(Process ID/PID)
- SI(Session ID)
- ProcessName(name of the running process)
- AggregatorHost(normal Windows process, related to system/app background activity)
- AM_Delta_Patch_1.417.483.0(Microsoft Defender update-related process. AM naming pattern is commonly tied to antimalware definition updates)
- amazon-ssm-agent(Amazon Systems Manager Agent, found on AWS EC2 Windows systems. Allows remote management through AWS systems manager)
- conhost(Console Windows Host, normal Windows process that supports command-line windows, such as cmd.exe and Powershell)

### Syntax: Get-Service

PS C:\Users\captain> Get-Service

Status   Name               DisplayName                           
------   ----               -----------
Stopped  Amazon EC2Launch   Amazon EC2Launch
Running  AmazonSSMAgent     Amazon SSM Agent
Stopped  AppIDSvc           Application Identity
Running  BFE                Base Filtering Engine
Running  CertPropSvc        Certificate Propagation
Stopped  ClipSVC            Client License Service (ClipSVC)
[...]

- details the current status of Windows services
- Status(whether the service is currently 'Running' or 'Stopped'
- Name(short internal service name)
- DisplayName(user-friendly name)
- Amazon EC2Launch(AWS Windows instance initialization service. Commonly used on EC2 machines for setup tasks, instance configuration, hostname handling, startup actions)
- AppIDSvc(Application Identity. Associated with AppLocker. If AppLocker is being used, this service oftem matters for application control policies
- BFE(Base Filtering Engine. Core Windows networking/security component. Supports Windows Filtering Platform. Foundational to fireall Behavior
- CertPropSvc(Certificate Propagation. Related to certificate handling. Relevant in environments using certificates for authentication.
- ClipSVC(Client License Service. Related to Microsoft Store/licensing -related functions)

