## Security Relevance
- Get-Process helps identify suspicious processes, unexpected shells, heavy CPU/Memory usage
- Properties such as Handles, CPU, ID are things shoudl be prioritiezed when lookingn for unusual activity
- Get-Service helps identify services that should be running, such as Defender/Firewall-related services
- Services may be used for persistence attacks making it critical to know whether critical protections are active
- Get-NetTCPConnections details what the machine is communicating with
- If a system is compromised it will probably be communicating to somewhere else
- Get-FileHash supports integrity checks, forensics and malware identification
- These cmdlets allow direct observation and ask better investigative questions
